00:35:21.960 --> 00:35:24.901
and of course you can do it
to the best of your ability.

00:35:24.901 --> 00:35:26.900
And the next thing that
comes out of your mouth,

00:35:26.900 --> 00:35:29.090
if it were me, would
be, by the way, are you

00:35:29.090 --> 00:35:30.470
talking to your wife about this?

00:35:30.470 --> 00:35:32.400
Are you talking to
your sister about this?

00:35:32.400 --> 00:35:35.030
Are you talking to your
daughter about her experiences?

00:35:35.030 --> 00:35:37.730
So that you're learning it--

00:35:37.730 --> 00:35:40.250
and learning it through the
prism of multiple women's

00:35:40.250 --> 00:35:42.230
experiences, if
that makes sense.

00:35:42.230 --> 00:35:44.090
And I will also
just add that there

00:35:44.090 --> 00:35:47.237
is nothing wrong with asking,
what can I do to do it better?

00:35:47.237 --> 00:35:49.320
You know, what can I do
to make it better for you?

00:35:49.320 --> 00:35:50.990
What can I do to make it
better for women generally?

00:35:50.990 --> 00:35:52.750
How can I be a better advocate?

00:35:52.750 --> 00:35:56.570
So I think it's not
just about how can I

00:35:56.570 --> 00:35:59.480
summarize what I'm
reading about, but also

00:35:59.480 --> 00:36:02.060
how can I propel men
to be more engaged

00:36:02.060 --> 00:36:05.000
in the conversation about what
healthier masculinity would

00:36:05.000 --> 00:36:07.740
look like, and how to make the
world a better place for women

00:36:07.740 --> 00:36:08.240
generally.

00:36:08.240 --> 00:36:09.810
Does that make sense?

00:36:09.810 --> 00:36:11.180
Yeah?

